data: {"logs": "\u256d\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udccb Task Started \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256e\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  Task Started                                                                \u2502\n\u2502  Name: Analyze the following infrastructure requirement and design a         \u2502\n\u2502  MINIMAL architecture.                                                       \u2502\n\u2502  Requirement: Create a production-valid Terraform configuration for Azure    \u2502\n\u2502  AKS with:                                                                   \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  * AKS private cluster NOT enabled                                           \u2502\n\u2502  * public Kubernetes API server endpoint enabled                             \u2502\n\u2502  * system node pool using Standard_D16s_v5 VM size                           \u2502\n\u2502  * node pool autoscaling enabled                                             \u2502\n\u2502  * minimum node count = 2                                                    \u2502\n\u2502  * maximum node count = 5                                                    \u2502\n\u2502  * minimum 2 subnets across different availability zones                     \u2502\n\u2502  * Virtual Network (VNet)                                                    \u2502\n\u2502  * subnets                                                                   \u2502\n\u2502  * route tables                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  * NSGs (Network Security Groups)                                            \u2502\n\u2502  * subnet associations                                                       \u2502\n\u2502  * NAT Gateway for outbound internet access                                  \u2502\n\u2502  * Azure Container Registry (ACR)                                            \u2502\n\u2502  * managed identity enabled                                                  \u2502\n\u2502  * required role assignments for AKS to pull images from ACR                 \u2502\n\u2502  * Azure CNI networking                                                      \u2502\n\u2502  * RBAC enabled                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  * OIDC issuer enabled                                                       \u2502\n\u2502  * workload identity enabled                                                 \u2502\n\u2502  * Log Analytics Workspace                                                   \u2502\n\u2502  * Azure Monitor Container Insights enabled                                  \u2502\n\u2502  * provider.tf and versions.tf                                               \u2502\n\u2502  * variables.tf                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  * outputs.tf                                                                \u2502\n\u2502  * Terraform azurerm provider v4+                                            \u2502\n\u2502  * code must pass terraform validate                                         \u2502\n\u2502  * code should be deployable without modification                            \u2502\n\u2502  * use best practices for production AKS                                     \u2502\n\u2502  * include tags on all resources                                             \u2502\n\u2502  * avoid deprecated Terraform arguments                                      \u2502\n\u2502  * use latest stable AKS version available from data source               