data: {"logs": "\u001b[35m[Finalize] todos_count=0, todos_with_results=0\u001b[0m\n\u256d\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 \u2705 Agent Final Answer \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u256e\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  Agent: Security & Compliance Reviewer                                       \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  Final Answer:                                                               \u2502\n\u2502  ### Security and Syntax Review Report: `azure-aks-production-public`        \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  **Status:** Validation Failed                                               \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  #### 1. Syntax Errors                                                       \u2502\n\u2502  The Terraform validation process failed due to an incorrect argument in     \u2502\n\u2502  the `azurerm_kubernetes_cluster` resource within `modules/aks/main.tf`.     \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Error:** `Unsupported argument \"enable_auto_scaling\"`                 \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Location:** `modules/aks/main.tf`, Line 19                            \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Correction:** The `enable_auto_scaling` argument is defined within    \u2502\n\u2502  the `default_node_pool` block, not at the root level of the                 \u2502\n\u2502  `azurerm_kubernetes_cluster` resource. Please move this argument inside     \u2502\n\u2502  the `default_node_pool` configuration block.                                \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  ---                                                                         \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  #### 2. Security & Best Practice Review (Preliminary)                       \u2502\n\u2502  Since the syntax error prevented a full plan, I have performed a manual     \u2502\n\u2502  review of the provided structure. Please ensure the following security      \u2502\n\u2502  controls are implemented:                                                   \u2502\n\u2502                                                                              \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Public Access (Critical):** The project name                          \u2502\n\u2502  `azure-aks-production-public` suggests the AKS API server or load balancer  \u2502\n\u2502  might be public.                                                            \u2502\n\u2502      *   **Action:** Ensure `api_server_authorized_ip_ranges` is configured  \u2502\n\u2502  to restrict access to the Kubernetes API server to known CIDR blocks.       \u2502\n\u2502      *   **Action:** If this is a production environment, strongly consider  \u2502\n\u2502  using an **Azure Private Link** for the AKS API server to keep traffic off  \u2502\n\u2502  the public internet.                                                        \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Encryption at Rest:**                                                 \u2502\n\u2502      *   **Action:** Verify that `disk_encryption_set_id` is configured for  \u2502\n\u2502  the node pools to ensure OS and data disks are encrypted with Customer      \u2502\n\u2502  Managed Keys (CMK) if required by your compliance policy.                   \u2502\n\u2502  *   **Identity:**                       